Long ago, before the humans learned to bend the world to their will,
Gaea created the Changing Breeds. Powerful beings borne of flesh and
spirit, the Changing Breeds had the task of safeguarding Gaea's creations,
both from the ravages of the spirit world and from their own selfish desires.
She created the Garou to be Her warriors, the Bastet to be her eyes, and the
Gurahl to be her protectors.

The Bastet are a collected group of Changing Breed who are based on the felines
of the world. These cats being most of the Big Cats: Panthers/Leopards, extinct
Cave-Lions, Jaguars, Tigers, Lions and Cheetah, to a handful of small cats:
Puma/Mountain Lion and Lynxes . The term Collected Group is used, due to fact
that unlike the Garou, whose tribes, though different in ideals and some
physical characteristics, are varied based on the different number of cats that
have been presented and for the Eyes of Gaea, whose very purpose is to learn and
keep secrets, that suits them just fine. After all, what goes on behind a cats 
eyes should be his own business. Bastet are blessed by Gaea with agility, and 
many other traits of their feline cousins.

The Gurahl are werebears. According to their lore, the Gurahl are Gaea's
original protectors, created to ward off the destructive power of the Wyrm, but 
when it grew too powerful for them they petitioned Gaea for help, and she
created the Garou. Slower to anger, the Gurahl are protectors rather than 
warriors. Gurahl are blessed by Gaea with strong wills, and many of the traits
of their bear cousins.
